Bonus Salary

You will receive a Christmas bonus equal to 1 month's salary

You will receive a vacation bonus equal to ⅓ of one month’s salary

Overtime Pay

Overtime will be paid as required by law.

Hours outside of standard work hours (40 hours per week is standard) are considered overtime. Employees can work a maximum of 2 hours of overtime daily. For additional hours, employees are paid:

- 150% of the hourly rate on weekdays

- 200% of the hourly rate on weekends and holidays

Paid Time Off

Vacation: 20 working days per year

National Holidays: 15 working days per year

Sick Leave: There is no maximum period for employees to take sick leave. This leave is paid at different rates and by different payers depending upon the length

0 - 15 days paid by the employer at 100%

15 days+ paid at 91% of salary up to a maximum amount. Paid by INSS.

Maternity leave

Pregnant employees are entitled to 120 days of paid leave, paid by the employer.

Paternity Leave

Employees are entitled to 5 calendar days of paid paternity leave. The employee will receive 100% of their average salary during this period, and the employer will be responsible for this pay.

We use Deel (www.deel.com) as our “employer of record” in Brazil. This means that Deel will be the official employer, and the paychecks and benefits will come from Deel.

Food card/ Meal Voucher = R$880 per month

Bonus Salary

You will receive a Christmas bonus equal to 1 month's salary

You will receive a vacation bonus equal to ⅓ of one month’s salary

Overtime Pay

Overtime will be paid as required by law.

Hours outside of standard work hours (40 hours per week is standard) are considered overtime. Employees can work a maximum of 2 hours of overtime daily. For additional hours, employees are paid:

- 150% of the hourly rate on weekdays

- 200% of the hourly rate on weekends and holidays

Paid Time Off

Vacation: 20 working days per year

National Holidays: 15 working days per year

Sick Leave: There is no maximum period for employees to take sick leave. This leave is paid at different rates and by different payers depending upon the length

0 - 15 days paid by the employer at 100%

15 days+ paid at 91% of salary up to a maximum amount. Paid by INSS.

Maternity leave

Pregnant employees are entitled to 120 days of paid leave, paid by the employer.

Paternity Leave

Employees are entitled to 5 calendar days of paid paternity leave. The employee will receive 100% of their average salary during this period, and the employer will be responsible for this pay.
